      "side": 1,
      "message": "`cue mod resolve` isn\u0027t affected: it only calls Resolver.ResolveToLocation, which remains purely lexical. The eager init added here lives inside the newRegistry func, which is only reached via ResolveToRegistry when a registry client is actually created - i.e. exactly when network access is about to happen. I\u0027ve added a `cue mod resolve` case to registry_lazy_config.txtar with the broken DOCKER_CONFIG in place to lock that contract in. Given that, I don\u0027t think a separate init-check method is needed, but happy to add one if you still prefer it.",
